Chaos broke out on Monday at Kamiti Maximum Prison between wardens and inmates, a senior warden at the facility has confirmed. The violent confrontation started at 5 am when inmates blocked wardens from carrying out a search in the prison. According to the official, the inmates engaged warders following the massive search which led to the recovery of SIM cards and phones. In prison, inmates squat in groups of five to be counted and checked by guards. At Kamiti, they have at least six headcounts per day. The first is conducted at 5 am, followed by another at 10 am, noon, 4 pm, 6 pm and 7 pm. More to follow...